Use `scheduleUpdateWithPriority`:

```typescript
class EnemyNode extends cc.Node {
    onEnter() {
        super.onEnter();
        this.scheduleUpdateWithPriority(1);
    }
    update(dt: number) {
        // move enemy - runs after nodes with priority 0
    }
    onExit() {
        this.unscheduleUpdate();
        super.onExit();
    }
}
```

Lower priority numbers run first. Default `scheduleUpdate()` uses priority 0. Setting priority 1 ensures this node's update runs after all priority-0 nodes.

