Pause the game layer node which pauses all actions and schedules for it and children:

```typescript
class GameScene extends cc.Scene {
    private gameLayer: cc.Node;
    private isPaused: boolean = false;

    onEnter(): void {
        super.onEnter();
        this.gameLayer = new cc.Node();
        this.addChild(this.gameLayer);
        // ... add game objects to gameLayer
    }

    togglePause(): void {
        this.isPaused = !this.isPaused;
        if (this.isPaused) {
            this.gameLayer.pause();
            // Pause all children too
            this.gameLayer.getChildren().forEach(child => child.pause());
        } else {
            this.gameLayer.resume();
            this.gameLayer.getChildren().forEach(child => child.resume());
        }
    }
}
```

Note: `pause()` on a parent does not automatically cascade to children. You must pause each child node individually.

`getChildren` returns direct children only. `enumerateChildren` can search recursively.

**`getChildren()`:**
```typescript
const directChildren: cc.Node[] = parent.getChildren();
// Returns only immediate children, not grandchildren
```

**`enumerateChildren(name, callback)`:**
```typescript
// Search direct children named 'enemy'
parent.enumerateChildren('enemy', (node) => {
    cc.log('Found: ' + node.getName());
    return false; // continue
});

// Search ALL descendants with '//' prefix
parent.enumerateChildren('//enemy', (node) => {
    // Finds 'enemy' at any depth in the subtree
    return false;
});
```

Use `getChildren()` when you know the node is a direct child. Use `enumerateChildren` with `//` prefix for deep searches in complex hierarchies.

Create a simple pool that recycles nodes instead of creating/destroying them:

```typescript
class NodePool {
    private pool: cc.Node[] = [];
    private createFn: () => cc.Node;

    constructor(createFn: () => cc.Node, preloadCount: number = 0) {
        this.createFn = createFn;
        for (let i = 0; i < preloadCount; i++) {
            this.pool.push(this.createFn());
        }
    }

    get(): cc.Node {
        if (this.pool.length > 0) {
            const node = this.pool.pop()!;
            node.setVisible(true);
            node.setOpacity(255);
            node.stopAllActions();
            return node;
        }
        return this.createFn();
    }

    put(node: cc.Node): void {
        node.removeFromParent(false); // don't cleanup
        node.stopAllActions();
        this.pool.push(node);
    }

    clear(): void {
        this.pool = [];
    }
}

// Usage:
const bulletPool = new NodePool(() => new cc.Sprite('bullet.png'), 20);
const bullet = bulletPool.get();
bullet.setPosition(100, 200);
this.addChild(bullet);
// When done:
bulletPool.put(bullet);
```

