Fix the bug. The normalized position doesn't center the node:

```typescript
const parent = new cc.Node();
const child = new cc.Sprite('icon.png');
child.setNormalizedPosition(cc.p(0.5, 0.5));
parent.addChild(child);
this.addChild(parent);
```

output:
The bug is that `parent` has no content size set. Normalized position is relative to the parent's content size. If the parent's size is (0, 0), any fraction of zero is still zero.

**Fix:** Set the parent's content size:

```typescript
const parent = new cc.Node();
parent.setContentSize(cc.director.getWinSize());
const child = new cc.Sprite('icon.png');
child.setNormalizedPosition(cc.p(0.5, 0.5));
parent.addChild(child);
this.addChild(parent);
```

Now (0.5, 0.5) correctly places the child at the center of the parent.
